{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1634725590,"nonce":"6O5TsoVecZFHTMIVILVtZse2VwQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s49d3_A","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4090","origin":"github"},"title":"Fix mandatory selects with checkboxes display","message":"Linter complains: `display=\"checkboxes\"` is incompatible with `optional=\"false\"`, remove the `display` attribute. \n\nThe problem is that select parameters are by default `optional=\"false\"`. If `display=\"checkboxes\"` is chosen the user can unselect all options which contradicts that the parameter is mandatory.\n\nI think that most of the cases are easy to solve, \n\n- If the code using the corresponding parameter checks for `None` then the parameter was probably intended to be `optional=\"true\"` and we can leave checkboxes. Otherwise remove checkboxes.\n- For other cases I think its necessary to check the underlying application if selecting no options is fine / not.\n\nHere is the list of tools that currently suffer from this (please put your name / link to the PR next to the tool if you are working on this): \n\n- [] tool_collections/snpeff/snpEff.xml\n  - effects\n- [] tools/augustus/augustus.xml\n  - outputs\n- [] tools/breseq/breseq.xml\n  - formats\n  - formats\n  - formats\n- [] tools/crispr_studio/crispr_studio.xml\n  - outputs\n- [] tools/cutadapt/cutadapt.xml\n  - output_selector\n- [] tools/deseq2/deseq2.xml\n  - output_selector\n- [] tools/egsea/egsea.xml\n  - base_methods\n- [] tools/genebed_maf_to_fasta/genebed_maf_to_fasta.xml\n  - species\n  - species\n- [] tools/genomescope/genomescope.xml\n  - output_files\n- [] tools/gffread/gffread.xml\n  - filtering\n  - merge_options\n  - merge_options\n  - ref_filtering\n  - fa_outputs\n  - ref_filtering\n  - fa_outputs\n- [] tools/goseq/goseq.xml\n  - fetchcats\n- [] tools/gubbins/gubbins.xml\n  - outfiles\n- [] tools/hmmer3/phmmer.xml\n  - ofo